article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 78, Cleveland St. 59
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Troy Cotton scored 19 points and Ryan Evanochko had 16 as Wisconsin-Green Bay beat Cleveland State for the third time this season, 78-59, in the first round of the Horizon League tournament Tuesday night. Fourth-seeded Green Bay (17-14) advances to the quarterfinals on Friday against fifth-seeded Youngstown State (14-16) in Dayton, Ohio. Cleveland State (10-21) was led by Bahaadar Russell with 14 points. The combined 35 points by guards Cotton and Evanochko helped the Phoenix end a two-game losing streak. Mike Schachtner added 12 points and seven rebounds and Terry Evans had 12 points, eight rebounds and six blocks for the Phoenix. Green Bay led 38-34 and went on a 16-6 run to open the second half. Cotton hit his fifth 3-pointer of the game to put the Phoenix ahead 52-40, and Evanochko stole the next Cleveland State possession and went the length of the court for a layup. Cleveland State hit just two of its first 11 shots of the second half. The Phoenix led 60-45 after Evans slammed home a Ryan Tillema miss with 7:53 left.
